MARANHÃO (2 berths):
S Imperatriz D (Imperatriz) [*]
Maranhão AC (Sâo Luís)

[*] Imperatriz lost the final match of 2007 Maranhão State Championship and received the
berth in Brazil Cup as state runner-up.
    Later, in 21/12/2007, Maranhão State FA proclamed Bacabal EC (Bacabal) as runner-up as
the state championship rules stated that the places from 2nd on would be awarded based on the
overall total of points won along the competition. CBF followed this decision and awarded the
berth in Brazil Cup to Bacabal in 15/01/2008.
    Finally, in 14/02/2008, the Supreme Sportive Court of CBF reawarded the berth in Brazil
Cup to Imperatriz.
